<i>noun</i>: 아브라함 <br>
<ul>
<li>
<i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>아브라함</dt><br>
<dd>the first of the Old Testament patriarchs and the father of Isaac; according to Genesis, God promised to give Abraham's family (the Hebrews) the land of Canaan (the Promised Land); God tested Abraham by asking him to sacrifice his son</dd><br>
<dd><i>synonyms</i>: Abraham, Ibrahim</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>
